Rating: 4
I've made this dish a couple of times now, and it is my favorite way to prepare any mild fish (couldn't find sea bream, but have used both halibut and sea bass). The artichokes and dressing really compliment the texture/flavor of the fish. Also, I tried this with frozen hearts, and it works fine, but the presentation isn't as nice. A fab dish for anyone who likes fish.

Rating: 4
This was an outstanding dish. I made it with whitefish. The only problem I had was that the artichokes tended to fall apart when I was slicing them. Next time I won't cook them quite as tender and let them finish cooking in the pan.

Rating: 4
Wow this is such a good recipe. The vinaigrete would be great on any fish. Start the artichoke broth mixture and then heat while prepping the artichokes. I left the stem on to have a better "handle" for ripping off all of the leaves and trimming the green parts off the heart then I trimmed the stem to about 1 inch because it was fresh not woody. I rarely use butter but I think it really makes the sauteed artichokes incredible. I cooked them 5 minutes and they were such a beautiful brown color and sooooo yummy. Much nicer than the picture. After making this once and being unsure it took longer now that I figured it out it's fairly simple and very gourmet. Now I want to see what everyone does with the aromatic artichoke broth that doesn't end up being used in the recipe. Mmmmm. This is a keeper.